      "Temperatures are the core controls, known by heart: fridges 0-5°C and freezers -18°C or below (checked and logged at least daily); cooking to 75°C core (or validated equivalent); hot holding at 63°C or above with the 2-hour rule for exceptions; cooling of cooked food fast (within the system's stated window, using shallow containers and cooling techniques, never the fridge-warming pan); reheating to 75°C core, once only; and probe thermometers cleaned, sanitised between uses and calibration-checked on schedule",
