      "The premises hold the standard: surfaces cleanable and maintained, the kitchen cleaning schedule (appendix) delivered and signed as done, pest vigilance per saf-040 at kitchen strength, waste out promptly (saf-036), and equipment maintained with failures escalated same-day (a broken fridge is an incident with a clock running)",
      "Small and domestic kitchens keep the principles at their scale: supported living and small-unit cooking uses the domestic-appropriate version — same temperature rules, same separation, same personal hygiene, simplified records — and staff cooking with people as enablement (teaching, supporting) hold the safety rails while sharing the task",
